<s> As I don't have all the RDF/OWL etc. syntax rules at my fingertips I can't comment on that part of the discussion, but I'd just like to slip in a mention of a long-standing issue, clarification of which might help understanding.  </s>
<s> When we are talking about a class or category of entities, such as "dogs", it is logical and clearer to use the plural form.  </s>
<s> Any definition or link is not to a specific dog, but to the attributes shared by all members of the class.  </s>
<s> A class may have sub-classes such as "spaniels" or "poodles", or specific instances such as "Fido", "Rover" or "Laika".  </s>
<s> It is important to be clear whether any URI is pointing to a category or to a specific instance.  </s>
<s> The convention of using the plural only applies to "count-nouns", to which the question "how many" is applicable.  </s>
<s> "Non-count-nouns", to which "how much" applies, like "water" or "love", are naturally expressed in the singular form.  </s>
